ellites:\n> "Our current operational rockets, including Falcon 9 and Falcon Heavy, **are not capable of deploying** V3 satellites and **V2 Mobile satellites**."\n\n> "Full reusability of Starship’s upper stage **is not required to deploy** our V3 satellites and **V2 Mobile satellites** in low-Earth orbit... Starship’s substantial payload capacity to LEO, even in partially reusable or expendable configurations, enables meaningful progress toward these objectives." \n\n> "...our ability to deploy next-generation V3 satellites, **V2 Mobile satellites**, and orbital AI compute infrastructure at scale... would be materially and adversely affected [if we are unable to successfully complete the development, testing, and deployment of Starship at scale in accordance with our anticipated schedule]."',
